Record Class SimpleLogEntry

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.dua3.utility.logging.SimpleLogEntry
Record Components:
time - the timestamp of the log entry as an Instant
loggerName - the name of the logger associated with the log entry
level - the LogLevel describing the severity of the log entry
marker - an identifier or additional metadata associated with the log entry
message - the message of the log entry
location - the source location associated with the log entry, or null if no location is specified
throwable - the Throwable associated with the log entry, or null if no throwable is present
All Implemented Interfaces:
LogEntry
public record SimpleLogEntry(Instant time, String loggerName, LogLevel level, String marker, String message, String location, @Nullable Throwable throwable) extends Record implements LogEntry
Represents a single log entry containing details about a logging event. This record implements the LogEntry interface and provides an immutable representation of a log entry with properties such as message, logger name, time, log level, marker, throwable, and location.
